gemini-1.5-pro.ocr_text:
GREAT SMOKY MOUNTAINS NATIONAL PARK
GSMNP10734

CAT. NO.
GRSM 113861

Plants of Tennessee
Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

Tennessee: Sevier County
35.66893° Latitude 83.39407° Longitude  2800 Ft. Elevation
Quadrangle: Mount Le Conte Middle Prong Little Pigeon River Watershed

The Great Smoky Mountains National Park. WGS84/NAD83. Porters Creek Trail. Take
US 321 5.9 miles east of Gatlinburg, Tennessee and turn onto the Greenbrier road at the
park entrance sign. Pass the ranger station and two picnic areas. At mile 4.1, park on a
traffic loop and look for the gate and trail sign.

Growing on south-facing (180°) wooded slope with *Acer rubrum*, *Betula lenta*,
*Liriodendron tulipifera*, *Magnolia acuminata*, *Tsuga canadensis*, *Rhododendron maximum*,
*Aristolochia macrophylla*, *Mitchella repens*, *Carex aestivalis*, *Juncus tenuis*, etc.
Evergreen.

38884 Loy R. Phillippe, Cassandra Allsap, Connie Cunningham, Grant Cunningham, Paul
B. Marcum
25 June 2006
